+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01ALNEmEmqxrft8Gs9uQzfn7","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Phase 7: Task Dependencies\n     2→\n     3→Add the ability for tasks to declare dependencies on other tasks, so they only become available once their prerequisites are done.\n     4→\n     5→## Requirements\n     6→\n     7→- When adding a task, you can specify a list of task IDs that must complete before this task becomes available.\n     8→- A task with unresolved dependencies is blocked and will not be returned when retrieving.\n     9→- When a dependency completes, the system should check whether any blocked tasks are now unblocked.\n    10→- Circular dependencies (direct or indirect) must be detected and rejected at task-creation time.\n    11→- Depending on a non-existent task should cause an error.\n    12→- A failed dependency does NOT automatically fail its dependents -- they remain blocked.\n    13→- There should be a way to inspect a task's dependency status.\n    14→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Jdc6eouudA957tNbSfCgvW","session_id":"82fad245-a271-4167-8a97-934a9c7f30f7","uuid":"533e91ba-cd1b-4e96-827a-5b6efd8e52aa"}
