+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Jdc6eouudA957tNbSfCgvW","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Complete Project Structure Overview\n\nI've thoroughly explored the project. Here's everything you need to know:\n\n### Directory Structure\n```\n/workspace/\n├── .git/                           (Git repository)\n├── .gitignore                      (Ignores: node_modules/, dist/, *.tsbuildinfo)\n├── .eslintrc.cjs                   (ESLint configuration)\n├── package.json                    (Project dependencies and scripts)\n├── package-lock.json               (Locked dependencies)\n├── tsconfig.json                   (TypeScript configuration)\n├── vitest.config.ts                (Test configuration)\n├── TASK.md                         (Project overview)\n├── phases/                         (12 phase requirement files)\n│   ├── phase-01.md\n│   ├── phase-02.md\n│   ├── phase-03.md\n│   ├── phase-04.md\n│   ├── phase-05.md\n│   ├── phase-06.md\n│   ├── phase-07.md\n│   ├── phase-08.md\n│   ├── phase-09.md\n│   ├── phase-10.md\n│   ├── phase-11.md\n│   └── phase-12.md\n└── src/                            (Empty - ready for implementation)\n    └── .gitkeep\n```\n\n### Package.json\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"bench-task-queue\",\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n  \"description\": \"Task queue marathon benchmark\",\n  \"type\": \"module\",\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"build\": \"tsc\",\n    \"lint\": \"eslint src/\",\n    \"test\": \"vitest run\"\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"@types/node\": \"^25.2.3\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/parser\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"eslint\": \"^8.56.0\",\n    \"typescript\": \"^5.4.0\",\n    \"@vitest/coverage-v8\": \"^2.0.0\",\n    \"vitest\": \"^2.0.0\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### TypeScript Config (tsconfig.json)\n- Target: ES2022\n- Module: Node16\n- Output directory: ./dist\n- Root directory: ./src\n- Strict mode enabled\n- Source maps and declaration maps enabled\n\n### ESLint Config (.eslintrc.cjs)\n- Parser: @typescript-eslint/parser\n- Plugins: @typescript-eslint\n- Extends: eslint:recommended + plugin:@typescript-eslint/recommended\n- Allows unused variables prefixed with underscore\n- Node and ES2022 environment\n\n### Vitest Config\n- Global test functions enabled\n- Test timeout: 10 seconds\n\n### All 12 Phase Requirements (Complete Content)\n\n**Phase 1: Basic FIFO Queue**\n- Accept payloads and return task objects with unique IDs\n- Task object must include: unique identifier, status, creation timestamp\n- New tasks start in \"pending\" state\n- Retrieving next task returns oldest pending task and transitions to \"processing\"\n- Return null if no tasks available\n- Provide way to check waiting task count\n\n**Phase 2: Named Queues**\n- Support multiple independent queues identified by name\n- Default queue used when name omitted\n- Each queue operates independently\n- Create queues implicitly on first task addition\n- List all existing queue names\n- Empty/non-existent queues return null\n- Backward compatible with Phase 1\n\n**Phase 3: Priority**\n- Priority levels 1-10 (1=highest, 5=default)\n- Retrieve higher-priority tasks first\n- Same priority returns in FIFO order\n- Invalid priorities cause errors\n- Per-queue priority ordering\n- Expose priority in task object\n\n**Phase 4: Delayed and Scheduled Tasks**\n- Tasks can have delay (milliseconds) or specific future availability time\n- Delayed tasks added immediately but not returned until available\n- Non-delayed tasks preferred over unavailable delayed tasks\n- Multiple delayed tasks ordered by: availability time → priority → FIFO\n- Task object indicates availability time\n- Works correctly with named queues\n\n**Phase 5: Retry with Backoff**\n- Mark processing tasks as completed or failed\n- Failed tasks auto re-added with exponential backoff delay: baseDelay * 2^(attempt-1)\n- Default max retries: 3 (configurable per task)\n- Default base backoff: 1000ms (configurable per task)\n- Track attempt count\n- Keep original queue and priority on retry\n- No retry if exhausted\n\n**Phase 6: Dead Letter Queue**\n- Tasks with exhausted retries move to DLQ associated with original queue\n- View all dead-lettered tasks for a queue\n- Dead-lettered tasks retain error info and failure count\n- Move dead-lettered tasks back to original queue for fresh retries\n- Clear all dead-lettered tasks for a queue\n- Each named queue has independent DLQ\n\n**Phase 7: Task Dependencies**\n- Tasks can specify list of IDs they depend on\n- Blocked tasks not returned when retrieving\n- Check for unblocked tasks when dependency completes\n- Detect and reject circular dependencies at creation time\n- Error on non-existent task dependency\n- Failed dependency doesn't fail dependents (remain blocked)\n- Inspect task dependency status\n\n**Phase 8: Concurrency Control**\n- Per-queue limit on simultaneous processing tasks\n- Exceeding limit returns null even if pending tasks exist\n- Completing/failing task frees concurrency slot\n- Default: no limit (unlimited)\n- Set and query concurrency limit and active count\n- Highest-priority available task chosen under concurrency limit\n\n**Phase 9: Progress Tracking and Cancellation**\n- Processing tasks report progress (0-100%) with optional message\n- Query task's current progress\n- Subscribe to progress updates with notifications\n- Cancellable subscriptions\n- Cancel pending or processing tasks\n- Cancelled pending tasks removed from queue\n- Cancelled processing tasks status updated\n- Cancelled tasks never retried\n\n**Phase 10: Recurring Tasks**\n- Associate cron expression with queue and task template\n- Support simple cron subset: `*/N * * * *` (every N minutes), `0 * * * *` (hourly), `0 0 * * *` (daily midnight)\n- Create, remove, list active schedules\n- Manual \"tick\" mechanism to evaluate schedules and enqueue due tasks\n- Recurring tasks subject to all queue rules once enqueued\n- Removing schedule stops future occurrences\n\n**Phase 11: Middleware Pipeline**\n- Register middleware per queue\n- Middleware intercepts and transforms tasks before handler\n- Each middleware receives task and \"next\" function\n- Not calling \"next\" skips processing\n- Middleware can modify task metadata/payload\n- Errors in middleware mark task as failed\n- Register processing function/handler per queue (invoked after middleware)\n- Independent middleware stack per queue\n\n**Phase 12: Graceful Shutdown**\n- Shutdown signal stops accepting new tasks\n- New task additions fail after shutdown initiated\n- Wait for currently-processing tasks (with configurable timeout)\n- Force-cancel incomplete tasks after timeout\n- Register callbacks during shutdown\n- Provide summary: completed tasks, force-cancelled tasks, shutdown duration\n- Multiple shutdown calls safe and return same result\n- Immediate completion if no tasks processing\n\n### TASK.md Overview\nBuild a fully-featured in-memory task queue system (12 phases). Think of it as a simplified Bull/BeeQueue/Celery equivalent with no external dependencies. All implementation exports from `src/index.ts` with no runtime dependencies allowed.\n\n### Current State\n- src/ directory is empty and ready for implementation\n- All configuration files properly set up\n- No existing source code to extend"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ab89bef (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 19365\ntool_uses: 23\nduration_ms: 30214</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"82fad245-a271-4167-8a97-934a9c7f30f7","uuid":"b4b54583-4205-4b4e-9aa1-2598fc66fe37","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the project structure thoroughly. I need to understand:\n1. The complete directory structure\n2. All files in phases/*.md - read every single one of them\n3. The package.json configuration\n4. The tsconfig.json configuration\n5. Any existing source files in src/