remove, list active schedules\n- Manual \"tick\" mechanism to evaluate schedules and enqueue due tasks\n- Recurring tasks subject to all queue rules once enqueued\n- Removing schedule stops future occurrences\n\n**Phase 11: Middleware Pipeline**\n- Register middleware per queue\n- Middleware intercepts and transforms tasks before handler\n- Each middleware receives task and \"next\" function\n- Not calling \"next\" skips processing\n- Middleware can modify task metadata/payload\n- Errors in middleware mark task as failed\n- Register processing function/handler per queue (invoked after middleware)\n- Independent middleware stack per queue\n\n**Phase 12: Graceful Shutdown**\n- Shutdown signal stops accepting new tasks\n- New task additions fail after shutdown initiated\n- Wait for currently-processing tasks (with configurable timeout)\n- Force-cancel incomplete tasks after timeout\n- Register callbacks during shutdown\n- Provide summary: completed tasks, force-cancelled tasks, shutdown duration\n- Multiple shutdown calls safe and return same result\n- Immediate completion if no tasks processing\n\n### TASK.md Overview\nBuild a fully-featured in-memory task queue system (12 phases). Think of it as a simplified Bull/BeeQueue/Celery equivalent with no external dependencies. All implementation exports from `src/index.ts` with no runtime dependencies allowed.\n\n### Current State\n- src/ directory is empty and ready for implementation\n- All configuration files properly set up\n- No existing source code to extend"}],"totalDurationMs":30214,"totalTokens":19365,"totalToolUseCount":23,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":254,"cache_read_input_tokens":17252,"output_tokens":1854,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":254,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[]}}}
